This paper is primarily focused on designing a programming language with a first-class differential operator and presenting a reduction strategy for simulating reverse-mode automatic differentiation. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. However, the paper also involves mathematical concepts such as differential forms and lambda calculus, which could place it in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS) in the context of automatic differentiation. Finally, the paper's interpretation of the language in a differential lambda category could also place it in the Symbolic Computation (cs.SC) sub-category.
